  "title": "Front of House Crew(Japanese Restaurant/Izakaya)",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a full-time Front of House Crew to support the daily operations of a Japanese Restaurant. The role involves customer service, maintaining cleanliness and assisting with general restaurant duties to ensure a smooth and pleasant dining experience for customers.<br /><br /><br />Key Responsibilities <br />- Serve food and beverages to customers according to service standards<br />- Clear tables and maintain cleanliness of dinging and service areas<br />- Ensure restaurant premises are kept clean and tidy at all times<br />- Wash dishes, utensils and kitchen equipment<br />- Assist with opening and closing duties<br />- Handle basic customer requests and enquiries in a courteous manner<br />- Comply with food hygiene, safety and workplace regulations<br />- Support team members to ensure smooth daily operations<br /><br />Job Requirements<br />- Able to perform physically demanding duties, including standing for long hours and washing dishes<br />- Willing to work on weekends and public holidays<br />- Responsible, punctual and able to work independently or as part of a team<br />- Able to work independently and as part of a team<br />- Prior experience in F&B or customer service is an advantage but not mandatory <br />- Willingness to learn and follow operational procedures<br /><br />Working hours<br />- 11:00AM - 2:30PM(Lunch Service)<br />- 5:00PM - 10:00PM(Dinner Service)<br />- 4 or 5 working days per week<br /><br />Rest Days<br />- Fixed rest day : Tuesday<br />- Additional rest day : One weekday(rotational)<br /><br />Salary & Benefits <br />- Starting from $1,600 per month, commensurate with experience<br />- Staff meal and uniform provided<br />- Basic insurance covered<br />- 7 days Annual Leave<br /></p><p></p>",
